Reasoning: The paper focuses on developing a sensing system for data collection and analysis of professional eSports athletes, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The study also involves analyzing gaze data, which falls under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the collected data, such as scouting and assessing eSports players, which could be categorized under computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
